wikipedia_page.main: Timothy Davies (17 January 1857 – 22 August 1951) was a British Liberal Party politician). He represented Fulham as a Borough Councillor, Borough Alderman, County Councillor, Mayor and Member of Parliament.

response: *Timothy Davies (politician) (1857-1951) Welsh businessman based in London, Mayor of Fulham, Liberal MP 1906-1920

The constituency was created in 1885. The Liberals had won the seat six times and the Unionists three times. It was a marginal seat in 1910 but in 1918 the Liberal MP, Timothy Davies surprisingly did not receive endorsement from the Coalition Government, which instead was given to his Unionist opponent. The result at that General Election was:

He was first elected at the general election in January 1910, but was defeated at the December 1910 general election by the Liberal candidate Timothy Davies. He regained the seat at the 1918 general election, but died in office in 1920, aged 52.
